title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Percentage of childless women, with a total of 7 data points.
Overall Percentage of childless women has increased over the Year
Percentage of childless women is roughly constant from 45_to_50_years_old to 40_to_44_years_old, and lastly rapidly increasing from 40_to_44_years_old to 15_to_19_years_old.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 25_to_29_years_old and 20_to_24_years_old.
Max Percentage of childless women about 96.9 was recorded at Year 15_to_19_years_old
Min Percentage of childless women about 15.0 was recorded at Year 40_to_44_years_old
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Percentage of childless women with a total of 7 data points. The chart has one significant trend.
This trend is increasing which exists from 15_to_19_years_old to 45_to_50_years_old.
